        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 8:30PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 829 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles south of Seneca, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Norris, Townville, Seneca, Pendleton, Lake Keowee, Central, Liberty,
Oakway, Clemson, and Six Mile.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
